  "original_lang": "si",
  "original_title": "\u0db1\u0dd0\u0d9a\u0dad\u0dca \u0d91\u0db4\u0dcf \u0d89\u0dbd\u0dca\u0dbd\u0dcf \u0d85\u0dc3\u0dca\u0dc0\u0db1\u0dd4",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Do not resign",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The Galumuwadora activists say that they will inform the President and the Prime Minister to hand over the letters of resignation immediately without waiting any longer for the resignation.",
        "That the auspiciousness of the people of the country to leave will not apply, and if they try to stay in power for one more day without resigning, they will not be allowed to do so. Mr. Wasantha Mudalige, convener of the Inter-University Student Council, representing the strugglers, said that people's rights will not be abandoned.",
        "He mentioned that after the departure of both President Gotabhaya Rajapaksa and Prime Minister Ranil Wickremesinghe, an all-party government should be formed, but an interim government that could fulfill the economic and political demands of the people with the participation of the activists.",
        "Mr. Mudalige said that if the political parties in the parliament try to build all-party governments, they will not allow it, and said that the people struggled, the youths were shot and died in the oil queues, not to give the all-party eight-bolts a chance to another hornade.",
        "He said this while addressing a press conference held today (10) at the cinema hall in Gota Go village, Galle mouth."
      ],
